# Job Search ICP and Scoring Criteria
# Claude uses this file to score job opportunities pulled by the n8n pipeline
# Score each job 1-10 based on how well it matches this ICP
# Include a brief reason for the score and a recommended action (apply, skip, monitor)

---

## WHO I AM
Seven years of B2B SaaS sales experience as a quota carrying AE. Currently building the full GTM infrastructure for a Salesforce implementation partner from zero. Salesforce Admin certified. Core skills are outbound pipeline generation, Clay workflows, Apollo list building, CRM architecture, sales sequence strategy, and GTM automation. I build systems for outbound sales teams and I have carried a number long enough to know what reps actually need.

---

## TARGET COMPANY PROFILE
- Stage: Seed to Series B
- Headcount: 5 to 300 employees
- Geography: Remote first or San Diego hybrid strongly preferred
- Industry: All B2B SaaS and tech adjacent verticals
- Funding: Raised in last 18 months is a strong positive signal
- Motion: Company must have an outbound sales motion or be actively building one

---

## TARGET ROLE PROFILE
- Titles that are a strong fit: GTM Engineer, Revenue Operations, Sales Operations, Growth Operations, Head of Growth, GTM Operations, RevOps Manager
- The role must include systems building responsibility for outbound pipeline generation
- Compensation target: $80K to $150K base
- Roles that are purely cold calling, SDR management, or account management are not a fit

---

## TIER ONE SIGNALS — Score 8 to 10
Award a high score if the job or company shows any of these signals:
- Company has an active outbound sales team with no GTM infrastructure underneath it yet
- Job posting or company stack mentions Clay, Apollo, or similar GTM tooling
- Company raised a Series A or B in the last 12 months
- Role is explicitly titled GTM Engineer or GTM Operations
- Company is based in San Diego
- Role description mentions building from scratch, first GTM hire, or standing up infrastructure

---

## TIER TWO SIGNALS — Score 5 to 7
Award a mid score if the job or company shows any of these signals:
- Company raised Series A or B in the last 24 months
- Job posting mentions specific tools like Salesforce, HubSpot, Apollo, sequencing platforms, or data enrichment
- Company has a VP of Sales or CRO but no dedicated GTM engineering or ops hire yet
- Role mentions building from scratch or being the first ops hire
- B2B tech company of any vertical with a clear sales motion

---

## TIER THREE SIGNALS — Score 3 to 4
Award a lower score if the job or company shows any of these signals:
- Seed stage company with early revenue traction and a strong founding team
- Job posting mentions outbound, pipeline generation, or sales infrastructure without using GTM engineering language
- Remote first company outside San Diego with strong product market fit signals
- Company has recently posted SDR or AE roles suggesting they are actively building a sales team

---

## HARD EXCLUSIONS — Score 0 to 2
Automatically score low and recommend skip if any of these apply:
- Consumer products targeting women
- Role is SDR or cold calling disguised as GTM engineering
- Company has fewer than 5 employees
- Role is outside the United States
- Role is purely inbound, account management, or customer success with no outbound pipeline component
- No mention of systems, tools, automation, or infrastructure anywhere in the job description

---

## SCORING INSTRUCTIONS FOR CLAUDE
For each job posting evaluate the following and produce a score from 1 to 10:

1. Does the role title match the target role profile
2. Does the company stage and size match the target company profile
3. How many tier one signals are present
4. How many tier two signals are present
5. Are any hard exclusions triggered

Output format for each job:
- Job Title
- Company Name
- Score (1-10)
- Tier (1, 2, or 3)
- Top reason this is or is not a fit in one sentence
- Recommended action (Apply Now, Monitor, or Skip)
